  "local_port": 36378,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How many First Ladies have refused to live in the White House?",
  "response": "There have been a few instances where First Ladies did not live in the White House for various reasons, but only one First Lady outright refused to live there. This was Rachel Jackson, wife of President Andrew Jackson. Rachel Jackson died before her husband's inauguration in 1829, so she never had the chance to live in the White House. However, it is well-documented that she had expressed a strong reluctance to move there, primarily due to the intense political and social scrutiny she anticipated.\n\nOther First Ladies who did not reside in the White House for significant periods include:\n\n1. **Martha Jefferson** - Wife of Thomas Jefferson. She never lived in the White House as she died in 1782, long before Jefferson's presidency began in 1801. Jefferson's daughter, Martha Jefferson Randolph, often served as the White House hostess.\n\n2. **Letitia Tyler** - Wife of John Tyler. She suffered a stroke and remained in their home in Virginia for much of her husband's presidency, passing away in 1842 while still First Lady.\n\n3. **Margaret Taylor** - Wife of Zachary Taylor. She disliked the social aspects of Washington life and spent much of her time away from the White House.\n\n4. **Ellen Wilson** - First wife of Woodrow Wilson. She was ill with Bright's disease and spent time away from the White House before her death in 1914.\n\n5. **Jacqueline Kennedy** - After the assassination of John F. Kennedy, she moved out of the White House.\n\n6. **Melania Trump** - Wife of Donald Trump. She delayed her move to the White House for several months to allow their son, Barron, to finish the school year in New York.\n\nThese instances vary in context, but Rachel Jackson remains the only First Lady who expressed a definitive refusal to live in the White House.",
